Currently, the code sample creates a database with @collation_database=utf8_general_ci@.  This potentially creates issues[1] when sorting some unicode languages.  A better approach would be to specify the collation.

<pre><code class="diff">
- CREATE DATABASE redmine CHARACTER SET utf8;
+ CREATE DATABASE redmine CHARACTER SET utf8 COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci;
</code></pre>

[1] http://stackoverflow.com/questions/766809/whats-the-difference-between-utf8-general-ci-and-utf8-unicode-ci

